  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Anxiety and depression are often present in patients with chronic heart failure (CHF). This
      study aimed to evaluate the influence of anxiety and depression on the physical function,
      disability, and quality of life (QOL) in CHF. This study examined the effects of 8-week
      home-based exercise on these parameters, and investigated the correlations between these
      outcome changes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
